mil.emp3.api.abstracts

Class Container

  • java.lang.Object
    • mil.emp3.api.abstracts.Container
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IContainer, IGeoBase, IGeoContainer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Feature, Map, Overlay

    public class Container
extends java.lang.Object
implements IContainer
    Container class serves as a base class for the Map objects including Map, Overlay and Feature. It implements some basic capabilities related to children, listeners and properties. A note on memory management: When an application passes a reference to a Container to the EMP via any of interface methods, the EMP Core doesn't clone the object, it uses and stores the reference to the object in its internal structures. Applications need to be careful when making changes to these objects. In many cases 'apply' methods are provided in the interface to allow the applications to control when a change is reflected on the map.

      • setName

        public void setName(java.lang.String s)
        Each Container has user specified name. There is no check in the EMP Core for duplicate names or any sort of validation. For icon based MIL-STD-2525 point features the name will display if populated. If the uniqueDesignation modifier is also populated and labels are turned on both will display with the name to the right of the uniqueDesignation. This is based on behavior we had to be compliant with legacy products.
        Specified by:
        setName in interface IGeoBase
